zuul/driver/bitbucketcloud/bitbucketclou.message:
If a file was deleted in a PR `new` will be `null` here in the json body and only the `old` will have any information. 

Here's what `f` looks like:

```
{
  "status": "removed",
  "old": {
    "path": "file/path",
    "escaped_path": "file/path",
    "type": "commit_file",
    "links": {
      "self": {
        "href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/org_name/repo/src/hash/file/path"
      }
    }
  },
  "lines_removed": 1,
  "lines_added": 0,
  "new": null,
  "type": "diffstat"
}
```

Closing a branch (deleting it, having the PR automatically close the branch, etc) does not include `push.links`. All you get is a structure like the below:

 {
  "push": {
    "changes": [
      {
        "forced": false,
        "old": {},
        "created": false,
        "truncated": false,
        "closed": true,
        "new": null
      }
    ]
  },
  "actor": {},
  "repository": {}
 }

I don't see that documented though: https://support.atlassian.com/bitbucket-cloud/docs/event-payloads/

I suspect in these cases you'd want to use the `old.links.html.href` which is the reference to the closed branch.

