tobiko/openstack/octavia/_waiters.py.message:
I think here to simplify the logic we should have separate waiters for each state and the caller should be in charge of handling exceptions (therefore I would remove raise_if_update_timeout and raise_if_active_timeout flags).
The other thing I would change the raised exception type. It should be a special one for this case of use instead of a very generic RetryTimeLimitError, therefore I would patch the wait_for_status function for it, then I would remove this function.

Waiters should be like:

 def wait_for_load_balancer_update(...)
     return wait_for_load_balancer_status(...)

 def wait_for_load_balancer_active(...)
     return wait_for_load_balancer_status(...)

 def wait_for_load_balancer_pool_update(...)
     return wait_for_load_balancer_pool_status(...)

 def wait_for_load_balancer_pool_active(...)
     return wait_for_load_balancer_pool_status(...)

 def wait_for_load_balancer_member_update(...)
     return wait_for_load_balancer_member_status(...)

 def wait_for_load_balancer_member_active(...)
     return wait_for_load_balancer_member_status(...)


Please note you could regroup all these functions in a Hierarchical way. For example load_balancer contain pools that contain members. Therefore waiting for a member could implicitly check for a pool that could implicitly check the load balancer. Therefore a smart implementation could be done in the stack classes as they already have a hierarchical relationship.

